4056	\begin{lemma}\leanok
4057	[Finite presentation cover from quasi-coherence (Route B, step B1)]
4058	  \label{lem:qcoh_finite_presentation_cover}
4059	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.qcoh_finite_presentation_cover}
4060	  \uses{lem:exists_finite_basicOpen_subcover, lem:quasicoherentData_mathlib}
4061	  Let \(X = \operatorname{Spec} R\) and let \(\mathcal{F}\) be a quasi-coherent
4062	  \(\mathcal{O}_X\)-module. Then there exist a finite family \(g_1, \ldots, g_n \in R\) with
4063	  \(\operatorname{span}\{g_1, \ldots, g_n\} = R\) and, for each \(j\), a member \(U_{\varphi(j)}\) of
4064	  the quasi-coherence cover with \(D(g_j) \subseteq U_{\varphi(j)}\) carrying a presentation of the
4065	  over-picture restriction \(\mathcal{F}.\operatorname{over} U_{\varphi(j)}\).
4066	\end{lemma}
4067	\begin{proof}
4068	  \uses{lem:exists_finite_basicOpen_subcover, lem:quasicoherentData_mathlib}
4069	  \leanok
4070	  Quasi-coherence supplies a quasi-coherence datum (Lemma~\ref{lem:quasicoherentData_mathlib}): a cover
4071	  \((U_i)_i\) of \(X\) together with a presentation of \(\mathcal{F}.\operatorname{over} U_i\) for each
4072	  \(i\). The cover-of-terminal-object condition translates to \(\bigcup_i U_i = \top\); feeding this to
4073	  the finite basic-open refinement (Lemma~\ref{lem:exists_finite_basicOpen_subcover}) yields finitely
4074	  many \(g_j\) with \(D(g_j) \subseteq U_{\varphi(j)}\) and \(\operatorname{span}\{g_j\} = R\). The
4075	  required presentation of \(\mathcal{F}.\operatorname{over} U_{\varphi(j)}\) is the one attached to
4076	  \(U_{\varphi(j)}\) by the datum.
4077	\end{proof}
