4079	\begin{lemma}\leanok
4080	[Restricting a presentation to a basic open (Route B, step B2)]
4081	  \label{lem:presentation_over_basicOpen}
4082	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.presentationOverBasicOpen}
4083	  \uses{lem:presentation_map_mathlib}
4084	  Let \(\mathcal{M}\) be an \(\mathcal{O}_{\operatorname{Spec} R}\)-module, let \(U\) be an open
4085	  carrying a presentation of the over-restriction \(\mathcal{M}.\operatorname{over} U\), and let
4086	  \(g \in R\) with \(D(g) \subseteq U\). Then \(\mathcal{M}.\operatorname{over} D(g)\) admits a
4087	  presentation.
4088	\end{lemma}
4089	\begin{proof}
4090	  \uses{lem:presentation_map_mathlib}
4091	  \leanok
4092	  The further over-restriction from \(U\) to the smaller open \(D(g)\) is a left adjoint, hence
4093	  preserves colimits, and carries the unit object to the unit object; the nested over-restriction
4094	  instances make it a functor between the corresponding categories of sheaves of modules. Transport the
4095	  given presentation of \(\mathcal{M}.\operatorname{over} U\) along this functor by
4096	  Lemma~\ref{lem:presentation_map_mathlib} to obtain a presentation of
4097	  \(\mathcal{M}.\operatorname{over} D(g)\). This step is independent of the bridge of step B3.
4098	\end{proof}
